sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User/Dashboard
    participant K8S as Kubernetes API
    participant Op as KubeRay Operator
    participant Head as Ray Head Pod
    participant GCS_Redis as GCS/Redis
    participant Worker as Ray Worker Pod
    participant S3 as S3 Storage
    participant Client as Client (Notebook/CLI)
    participant Auto as Ray Autoscaler
    participant Prom as Prometheus

    Note over User,Worker: Flow 1: RayCluster Creation
    User->>K8S: Create RayCluster CR (6443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+)
    K8S-->>User: 201 Created

    K8S->>Op: Watch event: RayCluster created
    Op->>K8S: Create Ray Head Pod (6443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+)
    K8S->>Head: Start Ray Head
    Head->>GCS_Redis: Initialize GCS (6379/TCP TCP TLS 1.2+ optional)

    Op->>K8S: Create Ray Worker Pods (6443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+)
    K8S->>Worker: Start Ray Workers
    Worker->>Head: Connect to GCS (6379/TCP gRPC mTLS optional)
    Head-->>Op: Cluster ready

    Note over Client,S3: Flow 2: Job Submission and Execution
    Client->>Head: Submit job via Dashboard API (8265/TCP HTTP TLS 1.2+ optional)
    Head->>Worker: Distribute tasks (6379/TCP gRPC mTLS optional)
    Worker->>S3: Load dataset (443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+)
    S3-->>Worker: Dataset
    Worker->>Worker: Process data
    Worker->>Worker: Exchange objects (2384/TCP gRPC mTLS optional)
    Worker->>S3: Write checkpoints (443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+)
    Head-->>Client: Job result (8265/TCP HTTP TLS 1.2+ optional)

    Note over Auto,Worker: Flow 3: Autoscaling
    Auto->>GCS_Redis: Check resource demand (6379/TCP gRPC mTLS optional)
    GCS_Redis-->>Auto: Need more workers
    Auto->>K8S: Request worker scale-up (6443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+)
    K8S->>Op: Watch event: Scale requested
    Op->>K8S: Create new Worker Pods (6443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+)
    K8S->>Worker: Start new workers
    Worker->>Head: Connect to GCS (6379/TCP gRPC mTLS optional)

    Note over Prom,Op: Metrics Collection
    Prom->>Op: Scrape /metrics (8080/TCP HTTP)
    Op-->>Prom: Operator metrics
    Prom->>Head: Scrape /metrics (8265/TCP HTTP)
    Head-->>Prom: Cluster metrics
